<subSubSection id="24CB1080FFAEFFF0FAB2AEFD8215FAEE" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="6C6E430BFFAEFFF0FAB2AEFD837BFDDA" blockId="26.[151,1437,150,574]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFAEFFF0FAB2AEFD815EFE49" bold="true" box="[199,315,403,429]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Remarks.</emphasis>
Previous records from the coast of São Paulo include Ilhabela (Ilha de São Sebastião), Guarujá, and Santos (
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFAEFFF0FB57AED981A4FE35" author="Moreira, C." box="[290,449,439,465]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="123 - 145" refId="ref70979" refString="Moreira, C. (1906) Campanhas de Pesca do &quot; Annie &quot;. Archivos do Museu Nacional do Rio de Janeiro, 13, 123 - 145." type="journal article" year="1906">Moreira 1906</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFAEFFF0FBBBAED98217FE35" author="Holthuis, L. B." box="[462,626,439,465]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="723 - 884" refId="ref64870" refString="Holthuis, L. B. (1974) The lobsters of the superfamily Nephropidea of the Atlantic Ocean (Crustacea: Decapoda). Biological results of the University of Miami deep-sea expeditions. Bulletin of Marine Science, 24, 723 - 884." type="journal article" year="1974">Holthuis 1974</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFAEFFF0F80AAED98380FE35" author="Severino-Rodrigues, E. &amp; Hebling, N. J. &amp; Graca-Lopes, R." box="[639,997,439,465]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="171 - 182" refId="ref78241" refString="Severino-Rodrigues, E., Hebling, N. J. &amp; Graca-Lopes, R. (2007) Biodiversidade no produto da pesca de arrasto-de-fundo dirigida ao lagostim, Metanephrops rubellus (Moreira, 1903), desembarcado no litoral do estado de Sao Paulo, Brasil. Boletim do Instituto de Pesca, 33 (2), 171 - 182." type="journal article" year="2007">
Severino-Rodrigues 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFAEFFF0F912AED983C5FE35" box="[871,928,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">et al.</emphasis>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
). This species is particularly important in commercial fishing, with greater fishing effort along the southeast and south of Brazilian coast (
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFAEFFF0FE9BAEB585FDFE11" author="Williams, A. B." box="[1262,1432,475,501]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="1 - 36" refId="ref82517" refString="Williams, A. B. (1986) Lobsters-identification, world distribution, and U. S. trade. Marine Fisheries Review, 48 (2), 1 - 36." type="journal article" year="1986">Williams 1986</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFAEFFF0FAE2AE9181E0FDFD" author="Dall'Occo, P. L. &amp; Bento, R. T. &amp; Melo, G. A. S." box="[151,389,511,537]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="47 - 52" refId="ref60319" refString="Dall'Occo, P. L., Bento, R. T. &amp; Melo, G. A. S. (2007) Range extensions for lobsters off the Brazilian coast (Crustacea, Decapoda, Palinura, Astacidea). Biociencias, 15, 47 - 52." type="journal article" year="2007">
Dall’Occo 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFAEFFF0FB65AE918123FDFD" box="[272,326,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">et al.</emphasis>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
; Santana 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFAEFFF0FB99AE918244FDFD" box="[492,545,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">et al.</emphasis>
2016). Sequences accession number (GenBank): CCDB 479—16S (
<accessionNumber id="7382DEE8FFAEFFF0FF7BAE9185F5FDFE" box="[1294,1424,511,538]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/MF490164" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">MF490164</accessionNumber>
), COI (
<accessionNumber id="7382DEE8FFAEFFF0FAA3AD4D813EFDDA" box="[214,347,547,574]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/OM672400" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">OM672400</accessionNumber>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFAEFFF0FB04AD4D8208FDD9" author="Mantelatto, F. L. &amp; Terossi, M. &amp; Negri, M. &amp; Buranelli, R. C. &amp; Robles, R. &amp; Magalhaes, T. &amp; Tamburus, A. F. &amp; Rossi, N. &amp; Miyazaki, M. J." box="[369,621,547,573]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="805 - 815" refId="ref68637" refString="Mantelatto, F. L., Terossi, M., Negri, M., Buranelli, R. C., Robles, R., Magalhaes, T., Tamburus, A. F., Rossi, N. &amp; Miyazaki, M. J. (2018) DNA sequence database as a tool to identify decapod crustaceans on the Sao Paulo coastline. Mitochondrial DNA Part A: DNA Mapping, Sequencing and Analysis, 29 (5), 805 - 815. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 24701394.2017.1365848" type="journal article" year="2018">
Mantelatto 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFAEFFF0FB86AD4D824EFDD9" box="[499,555,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
; present study).
</paragraph>
<caption id="38AE1383FFAEFFF0FAE2AB778212FB7A" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6399742" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6399742" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6399742/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" startId="26.[151,250,1049,1073]" targetBox="[151,1436,594,1023]" targetPageId="26">
